==Deaths==
* [[217]] &ndash; [[Caracalla]], Roman emperor (b. 188)
* [[622]] &ndash; [[Prince Shōtoku]] of Japan (b. 572)
* [[632]] &ndash; [[Charibert II]], king of [[Aquitaine]]
* [[956]] &ndash; [[Gilbert, Duke of Burgundy]]
*[[1143]] &ndash; [[John II Komnenos]], Byzantine emperor (b. 1087)
*[[1364]] &ndash; [[John II of France]] (b. 1319)
*[[1450]] &ndash; [[Sejong the Great]], Korean king (b. 1397)
*[[1461]] &ndash; [[Georg von Peuerbach]], German mathematician and astronomer (b. 1423)
*[[1551]] &ndash; [[Oda Nobuhide]], Japanese warlord (b. 1510)
*[[1586]] &ndash; [[Martin Chemnitz]], Lutheran theologian and reformer (b. 1522)
*[[1612]] &ndash; [[Anne Catherine of Brandenburg]] (b. 1575)
*[[1691]] &ndash; [[Carlo Rainaldi]], Italian architect, designed the [[Santa Maria dei Miracoli and Santa Maria in Montesanto]] (b. 1611)
*[[1697]] &ndash; [[Niels Juel]], Norwegian-Danish admiral (b. 1629)
*[[1704]] &ndash; [[Hiob Ludolf]], German orientalist (b. 1624)
*  1704   &ndash; [[Henry Sydney, 1st Earl of Romney]], French-English politician (b. 1641)
*[[1725]] &ndash; [[John Wise (clergyman)|John Wise]], American clergyman (b. 1652)
*[[1735]] &ndash; [[Francis II Rákóczi]], Hungarian prince (b. 1676)
*[[1848]] &ndash; [[Gaetano Donizetti]], Italian composer (b. 1797)
*[[1857]] &ndash; [[Mangal Pandey]], Indian soldier (b. 1827)
*[[1861]] &ndash; [[Elisha Otis]], American businessman, founded the [[Otis Elevator Company]] (b. 1811)
*[[1870]] &ndash; [[Charles Auguste de Bériot]], Belgian violinist and composer (b. 1802)
*[[1894]] &ndash; [[Bankim Chandra Chattopadhyay]], Indian author (b. 1838)
*[[1906]] &ndash; [[Auguste Deter]], German woman, first person diagnosed with [[Alzheimer's disease]] (b. 1850)
*[[1919]] &ndash; [[Loránd Eötvös]], Hungarian physicist (b. 1848)
*[[1920]] &ndash; [[Charles Griffes]], American pianist and composer (b. 1884)
*[[1925]] &ndash; [[Thecla Åhlander]], Swedish actress (b. 1855)
*[[1931]] &ndash; [[Erik Axel Karlfeldt]], Swedish poet, [[Nobel Prize in Literature|Nobel Prize]] laureate (b. 1864)
*[[1936]] &ndash; [[Robert Bárány]], Austrian physician, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] laureate (b. 1876)
*[[1942]] &ndash; [[Kostas Skarvelis]], Greek composer (b. 1880)
*[[1947]] &ndash; [[Olaf Frydenlund]], Norwegian target shooter (b. 1862)
*[[1950]] &ndash; [[Vaslav Nijinsky]], Polish dancer and choreographer (b. 1890)
*[[1958]] &ndash; [[Ethel Turner]], Australian author (b. 1872)
*[[1962]] &ndash; [[Juan Belmonte]], Spanish bullfighter (b. 1892)
*[[1965]] &ndash; [[Lars Hanson]], Swedish actor (b. 1886)
*[[1968]] &ndash; [[Barbara Jane Harrison]], English flight attendant (b. 1945)
*[[1973]] &ndash; [[Pablo Picasso]], Spanish painter and sculptor (b. 1881)
*[[1974]] &ndash; [[James Charles McGuigan]], Canadian cardinal (b. 1894)
*[[1978]] &ndash; [[Ford Frick]], American businessman (b. 1894)
*[[1981]] &ndash; [[Omar Bradley]], American general (b. 1893)
*[[1984]] &ndash; [[Pyotr Kapitsa]], Russian physicist, [[Nobel Prize in Physics|Nobel Prize]] laureate (b. 1894)
*[[1985]] &ndash; [[John Frederick Coots]], American songwriter (b. 1897)
*[[1986]] &ndash; [[Yukiko Okada]], Japanese singer and actress (b. 1967)
*[[1990]] &ndash; [[Ryan White]], American activist, inspired the [[Ryan White Care Act]] (b. 1971)
*[[1991]] &ndash; [[Per "Dead" Ohlin]], Swedish singer-songwriter and guitarist ([[Mayhem (band)|Mayhem]] and [[Morbid (band)|Morbid]]) (b. 1969)
*[[1992]] &ndash; [[Daniel Bovet]], Swiss pharmacologist, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] laureate (b. 1907)
*[[1993]] &ndash; [[Marian Anderson]], American singer (b. 1897)
*[[1994]] &ndash; [[François Rozet]], French-Canadian actor (b. 1899)
*[[1996]] &ndash; [[George W. Jenkins]], American businessman and philanthropist, founded [[Publix|Publix Super Markets]] (b. 1907)
*  1996   &ndash; [[Ben Johnson (actor)|Ben Johnson]], American actor and stuntman (b. 1918)
*  1996   &ndash; [[León Klimovsky]], Argentinian director (b. 1906)
*[[1997]] &ndash; [[Laura Nyro]], American singer-songwriter and pianist (b. 1947)
*[[2000]] &ndash; [[František Šťastný]], Czech motorcycle racer (b. 1927)
*  2000   &ndash; [[Claire Trevor]], American actress (b. 1910)
*[[2002]] &ndash; [[María Félix]], Mexican actress (b. 1914)
*[[2004]] &ndash; [[Enda Colleran]], Irish footballer and manager (b. 1941)
*[[2005]] &ndash; [[Eddie Miksis]], American baseball player (b. 1926)
*  2005   &ndash; [[Onna White]], Canadian dancer and choreographer (b. 1924)
*[[2006]] &ndash; [[Gerard Reve]], Dutch author (b. 1923)
*[[2007]] &ndash; [[Sol LeWitt]], American painter and sculptor (b. 1928)
*[[2008]] &ndash; [[Timothy Beaumont, Baron Beaumont of Whitley]], English clergyman and politician (b. 1928)
*  2008   &ndash; [[John Button]], Australian politician (b. 1933)
*  2008   &ndash; [[Stanley Kamel]], American actor (b. 1943)
*[[2009]] &ndash; [[Piotr Morawski]], Polish mountaineer (b. 1976)
*[[2010]] &ndash; [[Jack Agnew]], Irish-American soldier (b. 1922)
*  2010   &ndash; [[Malcolm McLaren]], English fashion designer and manager (b. 1946)
*  2010   &ndash; [[Teddy Scholten]], Dutch singer (b. 1926)
*[[2011]] &ndash; [[Hedda Sterne]], Romanian-American painter (b. 1910)
*[[2012]] &ndash; [[Bram Bart]], Dutch voice actor (b. 1962)
*[[2013]] &ndash; [[Mikhail Beketov]], Russian journalist (b. 1958)
*  2013   &ndash; [[Leslie Broderick]], English lieutenant (b. 1921)
*  2013   &ndash; [[Richard Brooker]], English actor and stuntman (b. 1954)
*  2013   &ndash; [[Anne Fitzalan-Howard, Duchess of Norfolk]] (b. 1927)
*  2013   &ndash; [[Annette Funicello]], American actress and singer (b. 1942)
*  2013   &ndash; [[Greg Kramer]], English-Canadian actor and author (b. 1961)
*  2013   &ndash; [[Sara Montiel]], Spanish-Mexican actress and singer (b. 1928)
*  2013   &ndash; [[Peter Reveen]], Australian-American magician (b. 1935)
*  2013   &ndash; [[William Royer]], American politician (b. 1920)
*  2013   &ndash; [[José Luis Sampedro]], Spanish economist and author (b. 1917)
*  2013   &ndash; [[Margaret Thatcher]], English politician, [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom]] (b. 1925)
*  2013   &ndash; [[Yasuhiro Yamada]], Japanese footballer (b. 1968)
