==Holidays and observances==
* [[Birkat Hachama]] (observed once every 28 years), last in 2009 and next in 2037 ([[Hebrew]])
* [[Buddha's Birthday]], also known as ''Hana Matsuri'', "Flower Festival" ([[Japan]])
* Christian [[Feast Day]]:
** [[Constantina]]
** [[Saint Julie Billiart of Namur|Julie Billiart of Namur]]
** [[Saint Perpetuus|Perpetuus]]
** [[Saint Walter of Pontoise|Walter of Pontoise]]
** [[April 8 (Eastern Orthodox liturgics)]]
** Middle date on which [[Easter]] Sunday can fall
* [[DABDay]] &ndash; Draw A Bird Day (International)
* Earliest day on which [[Public holidays in Liberia|Fast and Prayer Day]] can fall, while April 15 is the latest; celebrated on the second Friday in April ([[Liberia]])
* [[International Day of the Roma]]

